# documentation-standards

## language and tone

- professional, precise, approachable
- active voice; concise
- avoid subjective descriptors; use measurable terms

## content quality

- honest, direct, factual; acknowledge limits
- no marketing/superlatives/buzzwords
- technically accurate; verify claims; precise terms
- audience-appropriate depth
- document what exists (not future plans)
- use descriptive link text (avoid "click here" or "see this")
- human-centered where relevant; concrete examples

## structure

- start with overview and purpose
- middle: implementation details and usage
- end: examples and troubleshooting
- logical flow, consistent terms

## accessibility

- always include alt text for images (accessibility requirement)

## consistency

- maintain consistent capitalization and punctuation across list items
- use consistent list formatting within the same list
